<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:02:27.662 --> 00:02:29.700
<i>♪♪ That's rising hope ♪♪</i>

00:02:29.766 --> 00:02:31.870
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:02:35.812 --> 00:02:38.851
[wind gently blowing]

00:02:38.918 --> 00:02:41.857
[footsteps]

00:02:55.417 --> 00:02:58.524
[digital rumbling]

00:03:07.007 --> 00:03:08.309
Come on, Miyuki.

00:03:08.376 --> 00:03:09.613
All right.

00:03:19.165 --> 00:03:20.267
[door clangs closed]

00:03:25.110 --> 00:03:26.245
[grunts]

00:03:27.615 --> 00:03:31.456
[Hajime] Why, hello there.
Nice to meet you, Tatsuya Shiba.

00:03:32.892 --> 00:03:35.531
And also her highness
standing next to you.

00:03:35.598 --> 00:03:37.702
Is that your
younger sister Miyuki?

00:03:38.303 --> 00:03:40.140
Are you the leader of Blanche
in Japan?

00:03:40.207 --> 00:03:41.744
Ah.

00:03:41.810 --> 00:03:43.614
How rude of me.

00:03:44.348 --> 00:03:46.620
Correct, I'm the leader
of Blanche in Japan.

00:03:47.387 --> 00:03:48.891
I'm Hajime Tsukasa.

00:03:50.762 --> 00:03:52.197
I see.

00:03:52.264 --> 00:03:53.333
Well, I"m going to go ahead

00:03:53.399 --> 00:03:54.803
and recommend
that you surrender.

00:03:54.870 --> 00:03:57.207
I advise you all
to put your weapons down

00:03:57.274 --> 00:03:58.978
and your hands
behind your heads.

00:03:59.044 --> 00:04:02.151
[laughing maniacally]

00:04:02.217 --> 00:04:05.357
If you really think that magic
is such an absolute power,

00:04:05.424 --> 00:04:06.994
then you're sadly mistaken.

00:04:07.762 --> 00:04:09.633
[chuckling]

00:04:12.371 --> 00:04:13.841
[Hajime] Tatsuya Shiba.

00:04:13.908 --> 00:04:16.647
It's in your best interest
to join us.

00:04:17.014 --> 00:04:19.218
Your ability
to perform cast jamming without

00:04:19.285 --> 00:04:20.588
the use of antinite,

00:04:20.655 --> 00:04:23.026
I'm keenly interested
in that technique.

00:04:23.894 --> 00:04:26.399
So using Miss Mibu
to make contact with me

00:04:26.466 --> 00:04:27.836
and having
your brother assault me

00:04:27.902 --> 00:04:29.004
was all just for this?

00:04:29.071 --> 00:04:30.373
[grunts]

00:04:30.708 --> 00:04:31.643
Oh, my.

00:04:31.710 --> 00:04:34.315
I do so like
an intelligent child.

00:04:34.381 --> 00:04:35.985
Yet the fact that you
were aware of that

00:04:36.052 --> 00:04:40.193
and still showed up here proves
you're a child.

00:04:41.162 --> 00:04:44.468
[Hajime] Tatsuya Shiba,
you'll join us as our comrade.

00:04:44.536 --> 00:04:47.642
[magical whirring]

00:04:52.886 --> 00:04:54.890
[chuckles]

00:04:54.956 --> 00:04:57.361
[Tatsuya] Consciousness
interference‐type magic,

00:04:57.427 --> 00:04:58.797
or Evil‐Eye.

00:04:58.864 --> 00:05:01.202
At least,
that's what you call it,

00:05:01.269 --> 00:05:02.539
but in reality...

00:05:03.039 --> 00:05:05.243
The hypnotic pattern of light
is projected onto

00:05:05.310 --> 00:05:06.713
your subject's retinas.

00:05:07.214 --> 00:05:09.084
It's a light wave
oscillation type.

00:05:09.151 --> 00:05:10.822
Magic invocation.

00:05:10.888 --> 00:05:13.259
‐ Hypnosis, nothing more.
‐ [gasps]

00:05:13.326 --> 00:05:15.798
[Tatsuya] Is that how you
replaced Miss Mibu's memories?

00:05:15.865 --> 00:05:18.002
Hey, Brother,
are you...

00:05:18.571 --> 00:05:20.608
Well, those
inconsistent memories of hers,

00:05:20.675 --> 00:05:23.279
so intense they couldn't
have been natural.

00:05:23.346 --> 00:05:25.618
[gasps]
Why, you‐‐savages!

00:05:26.687 --> 00:05:28.389
[Hajime] How dare you?

00:05:28.456 --> 00:05:30.427
You do know you're pathetic,
right?

00:05:31.028 --> 00:05:32.331
<i>[Tatsuya] You try</i>
<i>to draw my attention</i>

00:05:32.397 --> 00:05:33.801
<i>to your glasses and away</i>

00:05:33.868 --> 00:05:36.607
<i>from your left hand which</i>
<i>was controlling the CAD.</i>

00:05:37.509 --> 00:05:39.613
As if I'd be so easily fooled.

00:05:39.679 --> 00:05:42.384
As long as I can see
the activation sequence,

00:05:42.451 --> 00:05:44.421
all I have to do
is delete part of it.

00:05:44.488 --> 00:05:47.461
Then that renders your
tacky spell nothing more

00:05:47.529 --> 00:05:48.697
than light signals.

00:05:49.098 --> 00:05:51.570
How did you do that?
I don't get it.

00:05:51.637 --> 00:05:54.509
Wasn't your magic counter attack
cast jamming, you bastard?

00:05:55.310 --> 00:05:56.345
Bastard, you say?

00:05:56.412 --> 00:05:58.082
So we're stooping
to name‐calling.

00:05:58.149 --> 00:06:01.422
Your pretense of greatness
has been stripped away.

00:06:02.124 --> 00:06:03.761
Fire!
Fire!

00:06:03.827 --> 00:06:06.065
[all gasping]
What the‐‐

00:06:06.432 --> 00:06:07.702
[Man] The hell's going on?

00:06:08.369 --> 00:06:10.641
[shuddering]

00:06:13.781 --> 00:06:15.217
[gasping]

00:06:15.283 --> 00:06:18.857
[screaming]

00:06:18.924 --> 00:06:21.028
Now, Brother.
You go after him.

00:06:21.095 --> 00:06:22.197
I'll handle this.

00:06:22.264 --> 00:06:23.499
All right.

00:06:24.335 --> 00:06:27.474
[all whimpering]

00:06:31.182 --> 00:06:32.652
Why, you‐‐

00:06:33.186 --> 00:06:37.094
[shouting]

00:06:37.962 --> 00:06:40.501
[Man grunting]

00:06:48.617 --> 00:06:50.086
You utter fool.

00:06:50.153 --> 00:06:52.090
[all gasping]

00:06:53.126 --> 00:06:54.796
Don't overdo it.

00:06:54.863 --> 00:06:56.900
It's hardly worth it
to get your hands dirty

00:06:56.967 --> 00:06:58.036
on their account.

00:06:58.403 --> 00:07:00.073
Yes, you're right.

00:07:00.140 --> 00:07:01.475
Hmm.

00:07:03.079 --> 00:07:05.584
[Miyuki] You all
are certainly out of luck.

00:07:06.285 --> 00:07:08.991
If only you hadn't raised hands
against my brother.

00:07:09.659 --> 00:07:12.632
I would have let you people off
with only a little bit of pain.

00:07:15.103 --> 00:07:16.339
‐ [Man] It can't be!
‐ [Man 2] What the hell?

00:07:16.405 --> 00:07:18.009
[Man 3 gasps]
My body!

00:07:18.076 --> 00:07:19.579
I can't move my legs!

00:07:20.447 --> 00:07:22.652
Please, you have to let us go!

00:07:23.019 --> 00:07:26.125
Just pray that you'll at least
be spared your lives.

00:07:26.192 --> 00:07:29.431
A wide oscillation
deceleration spell!

00:07:29.498 --> 00:07:31.135
She's using Niflheim!

00:07:46.432 --> 00:07:47.969
[gasps]

00:07:48.036 --> 00:07:49.204
[exhales sharply]

00:07:50.006 --> 00:07:50.975
[exhales]

00:07:54.148 --> 00:07:57.622
[gunfire]

00:07:57.689 --> 00:08:00.528
<i>[techno music]</i>

00:08:00.594 --> 00:08:02.464
Kirihara!
Go!

00:08:02.532 --> 00:08:05.003
[shouting]

00:08:05.070 --> 00:08:06.005
[gasps]

00:08:06.072 --> 00:08:07.107
[groans]

00:08:08.076 --> 00:08:09.211
[grunts]

00:08:10.380 --> 00:08:11.883
[both grunting]

00:08:12.150 --> 00:08:13.052
[snarls]

00:08:13.119 --> 00:08:15.758
[blows landing]
[all groaning]

00:08:17.194 --> 00:08:19.131
‐ [grunts]
‐ [Katsuto] Kirihara.

00:08:19.198 --> 00:08:20.166
Hmm?
[grunts]

00:08:21.068 --> 00:08:22.170
Let's go.

00:08:24.475 --> 00:08:25.511
[exhales sharply]

00:08:25.578 --> 00:08:26.747
[grunts]

00:08:37.334 --> 00:08:40.240
[digital whooshing]

00:08:46.252 --> 00:08:47.421
[gasps]

00:08:47.487 --> 00:08:48.657
[Man] Our weapons!

00:08:48.724 --> 00:08:50.661
[all gasping]
[door clanging open]

00:08:53.967 --> 00:08:55.336
[gasping]

00:08:55.403 --> 00:08:58.677
[chuckles nervously]

00:09:01.650 --> 00:09:03.654
[Hajime] What do you think,
magician?

00:09:03.721 --> 00:09:05.725
Actual cast jamming?

00:09:06.092 --> 00:09:08.029
<i>[Tatsuya] That's a lot</i>
<i>of antinite‐‐</i>

00:09:08.096 --> 00:09:11.235
<i>a military resource made</i>
<i>by ancient civilizations</i>

00:09:11.302 --> 00:09:13.072
<i>at high altitudes.</i>

00:09:13.707 --> 00:09:16.178
Your patrons
are the breakaway regimes

00:09:16.245 --> 00:09:17.214
of Ukraine‐Belarus...

00:09:17.280 --> 00:09:18.282
[gasps]

00:09:18.349 --> 00:09:19.384
[Tatsuya] And your sponsor,

00:09:19.451 --> 00:09:20.921
the Great Asian Alliance?

00:09:20.988 --> 00:09:21.790
[gasps]

00:09:21.857 --> 00:09:23.192
Destroy him!
[guns cocking]

00:09:26.666 --> 00:09:28.169
[all shouting]

00:09:28.236 --> 00:09:29.171
[gasps]

00:09:29.806 --> 00:09:30.775
[Man screaming]

00:09:30.841 --> 00:09:32.377
[shudders]
Impossible!

00:09:32.444 --> 00:09:34.047
How can you cast
spell invocations

00:09:34.114 --> 00:09:35.918
while under cast jamming?
[grunts]

00:09:35.985 --> 00:09:37.187
[screams]

00:09:48.109 --> 00:09:50.280
[Takeaki] Not too shabby,
big bro Shiba.

00:09:51.015 --> 00:09:53.252
So then,
who's this dude?

00:09:53.319 --> 00:09:56.225
[Tatsuya] Blanche's leader,
Hajime Tsukasa.

00:09:56.726 --> 00:09:57.762
Is it now?

00:09:57.829 --> 00:09:59.264
[whimpering]

00:09:59.331 --> 00:10:00.935
You're the bastard!

00:10:01.001 --> 00:10:02.204
[screams]

00:10:02.270 --> 00:10:05.143
This is the son of a bitch
who brainwashed Sayaka!

00:10:06.445 --> 00:10:11.890
[blow lands]
[Hajime screams]

00:10:11.957 --> 00:10:13.694
[Katsuto] Better stop
right there.

00:10:13.760 --> 00:10:19.338
[Hajime screaming]

00:10:20.941 --> 00:10:23.346
[magical whooshing]

00:10:24.616 --> 00:10:26.352
Did we get them all, Shiba?

00:10:27.287 --> 00:10:28.322
Most likely.

00:10:38.844 --> 00:10:41.950
<i>[weapon clicks]</i>

00:10:43.452 --> 00:10:44.989
[distant sirens blaring]

00:10:45.056 --> 00:10:46.860
[Leonhard] So I guess it's over,
huh?

00:10:46.927 --> 00:10:49.331
‐ What a letdown.
‐ Total bummer.

00:10:49.398 --> 00:10:52.370
The two of us came all this way
to get left on the sidelines.

00:10:52.437 --> 00:10:54.776
[Leonhard] Well, it's not like
the chairman and Tatsuya

00:10:54.843 --> 00:10:56.580
would let anyone slip through
the cracks.

00:10:56.646 --> 00:10:59.351
Yeah, and having to hold down
the fort with you made it feel

00:10:59.418 --> 00:11:00.521
like even more of a bummer.

00:11:00.588 --> 00:11:01.723
What'd you just say?

00:11:01.790 --> 00:11:02.758
‐ [chuckles]
‐ [gasps]

00:11:02.825 --> 00:11:04.061
‐ Brother!
‐ Mm?

00:11:08.135 --> 00:11:10.106
Are you okay?
Did you hurt yourself?

00:11:10.541 --> 00:11:11.710
Don't worry.
I'm all good.

00:11:11.776 --> 00:11:12.945
[exhales sharply]

00:11:15.149 --> 00:11:16.085
[exhales sharply]

00:11:17.053 --> 00:11:19.692
[Miyuki] Brother, I...

00:11:20.561 --> 00:11:21.663
[Tatsuya] It's all right.

00:11:21.730 --> 00:11:22.965
Huh?

00:11:30.380 --> 00:11:32.150
[gasping]

00:11:32.652 --> 00:11:33.787
[chuckles]

00:11:33.854 --> 00:11:35.323
Thank you, Brother!

00:11:35.390 --> 00:11:36.960
[exhales]

00:11:38.462 --> 00:11:40.099
It means more than you know.

00:11:48.784 --> 00:11:49.953
[Tatsuya] So.

00:11:50.386 --> 00:11:52.190
You've recovered
from your injuries, then.

00:11:52.257 --> 00:11:53.560
[Sayaka] Yes.

00:11:54.294 --> 00:11:56.566
The wound I got from that battle
with Miss Chiba

00:11:56.633 --> 00:11:58.035
wasn't a big deal to begin with.

00:11:59.204 --> 00:12:01.576
But do you remember how I
was completely wrong

00:12:01.643 --> 00:12:03.246
about Miss Watanabe before?

00:12:03.312 --> 00:12:05.316
To make sure that none
of my other memories

00:12:05.383 --> 00:12:06.653
are that messed up,

00:12:06.720 --> 00:12:08.389
they said I need to stay
in the hospital

00:12:08.456 --> 00:12:09.491
for a little longer.

00:12:11.262 --> 00:12:13.099
[Tatsuya] Kendo team
captain Tsukasa

00:12:13.165 --> 00:12:15.336
has been hospitalized
for that same reason.

00:12:15.871 --> 00:12:17.173
[Sayaka] He has?

00:12:17.474 --> 00:12:19.244
[Tatsuya] But under
the circumstances,

00:12:19.311 --> 00:12:22.384
I hear no criminal charges
are being brought against him.

00:12:22.752 --> 00:12:24.187
‐ [exhales]
‐ [Tatsuya] Of course,

00:12:24.254 --> 00:12:25.624
it looks like none
of the students

00:12:25.691 --> 00:12:27.093
at our school
will be reprimanded

00:12:27.160 --> 00:12:28.530
for their roles
in this incident.

00:12:28.597 --> 00:12:29.666
[gasps]

00:12:29.966 --> 00:12:31.402
Are you serious?

00:12:31.468 --> 00:12:32.605
I am,

00:12:32.672 --> 00:12:34.174
so you don't need
to worry anymore

00:12:34.241 --> 00:12:36.513
about being prosecuted
for conspiring with any

00:12:36.579 --> 00:12:37.748
of those people, either.

00:12:37.815 --> 00:12:39.117
[gasps]

00:12:39.184 --> 00:12:40.453
[Tatsuya] Since
the school's accountability

00:12:40.521 --> 00:12:41.923
would come under scrutiny,

00:12:41.990 --> 00:12:43.694
they seem to want
to keep it under wraps.

00:12:43.760 --> 00:12:45.029
Hmm.

00:12:48.770 --> 00:12:50.073
[Tatsuya] Anyway,

00:12:50.139 --> 00:12:52.310
when do you think
the doctors will discharge you?

00:12:52.377 --> 00:12:56.085
Mm, well,
it's supposed to be around May.

00:12:56.385 --> 00:12:57.588
[Tatsuya] I see.

00:12:57.655 --> 00:13:00.093
And please let me know
when you have the exact date.

00:13:00.561 --> 00:13:02.832
I'll be coming to help
you celebrate getting out.

00:13:03.600 --> 00:13:05.203
[giggles]

00:13:05.269 --> 00:13:06.973
Wow, that's so considerate
of you.

00:13:08.577 --> 00:13:09.879
[Sayaka] Thanks, Shiba.

00:13:09.946 --> 00:13:11.883
When I know which day
I'll be leaving,

00:13:11.950 --> 00:13:13.252
I'll let you know.

00:13:19.832 --> 00:13:22.705
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

00:13:22.772 --> 00:13:25.778
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:13:25.844 --> 00:13:27.113
[Tatsuya] Mr. Hayama.

00:13:29.017 --> 00:13:30.788
<i>[Maya] Oh, really?</i>

00:13:31.322 --> 00:13:33.760
<i>All Tatsuya did</i>
<i>was fulfill his duty</i>

00:13:33.827 --> 00:13:35.831
<i>as Miyuki's guardian, eh?</i>

00:13:37.067 --> 00:13:38.469
[Tadanori] Do you think
it would be wise

00:13:38.537 --> 00:13:40.239
to leave things as they are?

00:13:41.910 --> 00:13:43.212
I'm fine with it.

00:13:44.414 --> 00:13:47.053
As long as he remains
Miyuki's guardian.

00:13:47.420 --> 00:13:49.224
[Maya] Tatsuya
can't possibly betray

00:13:49.291 --> 00:13:51.228
the Yotsuba family,
after all.

00:13:51.996 --> 00:13:55.103
[birds chirping]

00:13:59.311 --> 00:14:02.017
[Miyuki] Isn't that Kirihara
over there with Miss Mibu?

00:14:03.085 --> 00:14:05.156
They seem very friendly
with each other.

00:14:05.223 --> 00:14:08.029
And apparently
he's been visiting every day.

00:14:08.329 --> 00:14:09.899
Really?
That's so surprising.

00:14:09.966 --> 00:14:12.003
[groans]
Fine, then.

00:14:12.070 --> 00:14:13.940
I guess there really
is no flustering you.

00:14:14.007 --> 00:14:15.309
Wrong.
I was surprised.

00:14:15.376 --> 00:14:16.478
Hmm?

00:14:16.546 --> 00:14:18.315
Who knew that Kirihara
could be so diligent?

00:14:18.382 --> 00:14:19.719
[Erika] That's not what I mean!

00:14:19.786 --> 00:14:22.892
Tatsuya, everything you say
and do is so twisted.

00:14:22.958 --> 00:14:25.129
No wonder Saya dumped
your sorry ass.

00:14:25.597 --> 00:14:29.639
Erika, why did you say Saya?
Are you talking about Miss Mibu?

00:14:29.706 --> 00:14:31.275
[Erika] Huh?
Obviously.

00:14:31.341 --> 00:14:33.513
You two have gotten
really chummy.

00:14:33.580 --> 00:14:34.582
[Erika] That's what I do.

00:14:35.383 --> 00:14:36.418
[exhales]

00:14:36.485 --> 00:14:37.387
Pardon, Miss Mibu?

00:14:37.454 --> 00:14:39.391
[both grunting]
Hi, Tatsuya.

00:14:39.926 --> 00:14:41.395
Hmm?

00:14:42.531 --> 00:14:44.669
Congratulations
on being discharged.

00:14:44.736 --> 00:14:45.904
Thanks, Miyuki.

00:14:46.338 --> 00:14:47.908
[Erika] Really, Saya,
you don't know how...

00:14:47.975 --> 00:14:49.746
Excuse me.
Are you Shiba?

00:14:50.313 --> 00:14:54.454
Hello, my name is Yuuzou Mibu,
and Sayaka is my daughter.

00:14:54.856 --> 00:14:56.225
[Yuuzou] Do you have a minute?

00:14:56.291 --> 00:14:57.494
Yes.

00:14:58.462 --> 00:15:01.001
[Yuuzou] I just want to say
I'm very grateful to you, Shiba.

00:15:01.536 --> 00:15:02.872
It's thanks
to you that my daughter

00:15:02.938 --> 00:15:04.141
was able to recover.

00:15:04.207 --> 00:15:06.178
[Tatsuya] Honestly,
I barely did anything.

00:15:06.679 --> 00:15:09.819
It was my sister and Chiba
who talked her through it.

00:15:10.687 --> 00:15:13.627
Truth be told,
I callously pushed her away.

00:15:13.693 --> 00:15:14.862
She should despise me.

00:15:15.430 --> 00:15:17.333
I don't deserve your gratitude.

00:15:18.670 --> 00:15:20.808
I could never bring myself
to show our daughter

00:15:20.874 --> 00:15:22.410
any tough love.

00:15:23.245 --> 00:15:25.016
<i>[Yuuzou] I was aware</i>
<i>that Sayaka's magic skills</i>

00:15:25.082 --> 00:15:26.786
<i>weren't coming along,</i>

00:15:26.853 --> 00:15:30.126
<i>but I never truly grasped</i>
<i>how much suffering</i>

00:15:30.193 --> 00:15:32.163
<i>it had been causing her</i>
<i>all that time.</i>

00:15:32.998 --> 00:15:35.971
Sayaka said that listening
to you open up made her remember

00:15:36.038 --> 00:15:37.641
<i>what it was to be torn...</i>

00:15:38.175 --> 00:15:39.745
<i>And that realization</i>
<i>shook her awake</i>

00:15:39.812 --> 00:15:41.415
<i>from the nightmare.</i>

00:15:41.816 --> 00:15:44.822
<i>She said when you assured her</i>
<i>she hadn't wasted her time,</i>

00:15:44.889 --> 00:15:46.091
<i>she was saved.</i>

00:15:48.730 --> 00:15:49.866
[grunts]

00:15:49.932 --> 00:15:53.139
So please allow me
to say thank you.

00:15:54.107 --> 00:15:55.376
I must insist,

00:15:55.443 --> 00:15:57.515
I didn't do anything
to earn your gratitude.

00:15:58.015 --> 00:15:59.417
Hmm.

00:15:59.919 --> 00:16:02.758
So you are indeed the kind
of man Kazama said you were.

00:16:02.825 --> 00:16:04.060
[gasps]

00:16:05.797 --> 00:16:06.933
Wait.

00:16:07.000 --> 00:16:08.870
You're acquainted
with Major Kazama?

00:16:09.437 --> 00:16:10.841
[Yuuzou] I'm already retired,
myself,

00:16:10.908 --> 00:16:12.978
but he's an old comrade
in arms who once shared

00:16:13.045 --> 00:16:14.447
a barracks with me.

00:16:15.249 --> 00:16:17.253
As for what Kazama told me,

00:16:17.320 --> 00:16:20.259
I won't say a word to anybody
so you can rest assured.

00:16:20.326 --> 00:16:22.932
I wanted to tell you
that my wife and I

00:16:22.998 --> 00:16:24.067
both know you were the one

00:16:24.134 --> 00:16:25.871
who really saved
our daughter's life.

00:16:25.938 --> 00:16:28.075
I genuinely hope you know that.

00:16:29.110 --> 00:16:30.614
You have my deepest thanks.

00:16:38.797 --> 00:16:39.966
[giggles]

00:16:40.032 --> 00:16:42.070
Huh?
Hey, Tatsuya!

00:16:42.136 --> 00:16:44.642
What was my dad just talking
to you about?

00:16:44.709 --> 00:16:46.513
[Tatsuya] That someone
who once looked after me

00:16:46.579 --> 00:16:47.380
when I was younger

00:16:47.447 --> 00:16:48.984
is a close friend
of your father's.

00:16:49.050 --> 00:16:50.988
That's pretty much
the gist of it.

00:16:51.288 --> 00:16:52.925
Oh, what a coincidence.

00:16:52.992 --> 00:16:55.329
Yeah, it certainly
is a small world.

00:16:55.396 --> 00:16:58.168
So Tatsuya and Saya really do
have a strong connection.

00:16:58.235 --> 00:17:00.306
It's like fate.
Hey, Saya,

00:17:00.373 --> 00:17:02.745
why did you jump ship
from the Tatsuya love boat over

00:17:02.811 --> 00:17:04.447
to Kirihara's?
Admit it.

00:17:04.515 --> 00:17:06.118
You were in love with Tatsuya,
right?

00:17:06.184 --> 00:17:07.955
Hey, come on now, Erika.
Stop.

00:17:08.022 --> 00:17:09.324
If it only came down to looks,

00:17:09.391 --> 00:17:11.495
I think Tatsuya
would obviously win, you know?

00:17:11.563 --> 00:17:14.100
You really take rudeness
to a whole new level.

00:17:14.167 --> 00:17:15.436
When it comes to men...

00:17:16.405 --> 00:17:17.975
Looks really aren't everything.

00:17:18.042 --> 00:17:19.411
[Takeaki grunts]
Seriously!

00:17:19.477 --> 00:17:21.181
You're gonna regret that,
damn it!

00:17:21.248 --> 00:17:23.553
[Erika] Gimmie a break.
Anyway, Saya,

00:17:23.620 --> 00:17:25.724
was Kirihara's persistence
the clincher?

00:17:25.791 --> 00:17:28.429
Did you get weak in the knees
over how awkward he is?

00:17:28.964 --> 00:17:30.166
[groans]

00:17:30.801 --> 00:17:32.237
Well, yes,

00:17:32.303 --> 00:17:34.174
if I'm going
to be honest with myself.

00:17:34.241 --> 00:17:36.779
I think I was in love
with him originally.

00:17:37.146 --> 00:17:38.282
[both gasping]

00:17:40.219 --> 00:17:41.789
He has something I admire;

00:17:41.856 --> 00:17:44.595
an unwavering strength
in his heart and his soul.

00:17:45.162 --> 00:17:48.068
Still,
even though I did respect him,

00:17:48.135 --> 00:17:49.538
he also frightened me.

00:17:51.141 --> 00:17:52.277
[grunts]

00:17:52.343 --> 00:17:54.715
[Sayaka] It wouldn't matter
how hard

00:17:54.782 --> 00:17:56.586
or fast I ran after him.

00:17:57.220 --> 00:17:58.924
In reality,
I could never,

00:17:58.990 --> 00:18:00.627
ever catch up to him.

00:18:01.295 --> 00:18:03.667
I could never get
as strong as him.

00:18:03.733 --> 00:18:04.702
[grunts]

00:18:07.608 --> 00:18:09.311
<i>[Sayaka] Kirihara, though,</i>

00:18:09.377 --> 00:18:11.883
<i>even if we fought sometimes,</i>

00:18:11.950 --> 00:18:13.853
<i>I thought that he was someone</i>
<i>who would always walk</i>

00:18:13.920 --> 00:18:15.423
<i>at the same pace as I do.</i>

00:18:16.358 --> 00:18:17.795
I guess that's the reason.

00:18:18.830 --> 00:18:20.466
[grunts]

00:18:20.534 --> 00:18:21.769
[giggles]

00:18:22.738 --> 00:18:24.240
That's a great story.

00:18:25.209 --> 00:18:26.746
So what about you, Kirihara?

00:18:26.813 --> 00:18:28.449
How long have you been pining
for Saya?

00:18:28.516 --> 00:18:30.486
[Takeaki] Man, give it a rest,
will ya?

00:18:30.554 --> 00:18:31.956
Who cares about that stuff?

00:18:32.023 --> 00:18:33.092
It's none of your business!

00:18:33.158 --> 00:18:34.629
Yeah, he's right, Erika.

00:18:34.695 --> 00:18:36.465
The amount
of time hardly matters.

00:18:36.532 --> 00:18:37.467
Huh?

00:18:37.534 --> 00:18:38.737
[Tatsuya] The important
thing here

00:18:38.803 --> 00:18:41.976
is Kirihara is seriously smitten
with Miss Mibu.

00:18:42.043 --> 00:18:44.014
‐ Wait, hold up!
‐ Oh, yeah?

00:18:44.080 --> 00:18:46.886
[Tatsuya] I can't go into detail
on account of confidentiality,

00:18:46.953 --> 00:18:49.625
but when I saw
the brave figure Kirihara cut

00:18:49.692 --> 00:18:51.763
while facing down
Blanche's leader,

00:18:51.829 --> 00:18:54.735
I knew I was simply no match
for him as a man.

00:18:55.570 --> 00:18:57.040
Do me a favor, Tatsuya.

00:18:57.106 --> 00:18:58.108
What is it?

00:18:58.175 --> 00:18:59.979
Tell me in secret later, okay?

00:19:00.413 --> 00:19:02.250
‐ [giggles]
‐ Man, you are such a gossip!

00:19:02.317 --> 00:19:03.385
You, too, Shiba!

00:19:03.452 --> 00:19:05.056
If you talk,
I'll make you pay!

00:19:05.122 --> 00:19:06.191
[Tatsuya] My lips are sealed.

00:19:06.258 --> 00:19:07.493
[Erika] Aww,
what does it matter?

00:19:07.561 --> 00:19:09.699
Shut up, Shiba!
[grunts]

00:19:09.765 --> 00:19:11.335
‐ [Erika giggles]
‐ [Takeaki] It does matter!

00:19:11.401 --> 00:19:12.437
‐ [Erika] Come on!
‐ [Takeaki] Get back here!

00:19:12.504 --> 00:19:14.074
[Erika] You can't catch me,
lover boy!

00:19:14.140 --> 00:19:15.176
‐ [giggles]
‐ [Takeaki] Gotcha now!

00:19:15.242 --> 00:19:16.612
[groans]

00:19:20.721 --> 00:19:21.656
[giggles]

00:19:21.723 --> 00:19:23.793
I can't believe
you just did that.

00:19:31.843 --> 00:19:32.811
[Miyuki] Brother?

00:19:32.878 --> 00:19:33.847
[Tatsuya] Yeah?

00:19:34.280 --> 00:19:35.650
Just so you know,

00:19:35.717 --> 00:19:38.556
I would follow you wherever
you go no matter what.

00:19:39.290 --> 00:19:41.261
[Miyuki] Even if you were
to rush off into

00:19:41.328 --> 00:19:43.232
the distance at the speed
of sound.

00:19:43.800 --> 00:19:46.204
Even if you were
to burst through the skies

00:19:46.271 --> 00:19:48.442
climbing even higher towards
the stars.

00:19:51.314 --> 00:19:52.316
[chuckles]

00:19:52.383 --> 00:19:53.953
If I had to pick one of us,

00:19:54.020 --> 00:19:56.826
I would argue I'm more likely
to get left behind by you.

00:19:57.661 --> 00:19:58.763
For now,

00:19:58.830 --> 00:20:01.368
how about instead of us reaching
for the heavens,

00:20:01.435 --> 00:20:03.439
we both try to keep our feet
on the ground?

00:20:03.907 --> 00:20:05.777
[Miyuki] Are you going back
to school now?

00:20:06.178 --> 00:20:07.380
[Tatsuya] Yeah.

00:20:07.447 --> 00:20:09.484
If I miss my practical
skills class,

00:20:09.552 --> 00:20:11.421
I'll have to make it up over
the weekend.

00:20:12.423 --> 00:20:13.927
Um, Brother,

00:20:13.993 --> 00:20:16.666
Isn't it hard on you having
to go to Magic School?

00:20:17.266 --> 00:20:19.605
If it were under
normal circumstances,

00:20:19.672 --> 00:20:21.943
there'd be no reason for you
to go to high school at all,

00:20:22.009 --> 00:20:23.412
considering your abilities.

00:20:24.782 --> 00:20:25.817
And despite that,

00:20:25.884 --> 00:20:28.122
you're allowing yourself
to become the object

00:20:28.188 --> 00:20:29.357
of people's scorn.

00:20:29.424 --> 00:20:30.861
You're forcing yourself
for my sake.

00:20:31.696 --> 00:20:32.664
Miyuki.

00:20:34.234 --> 00:20:36.973
[Tatsuya] No one's twisting
my arm to make me be here.

00:20:37.674 --> 00:20:39.779
'Cause I know right now's
the only time

00:20:39.845 --> 00:20:41.849
I'll have
to experience ordinary life.

00:20:41.916 --> 00:20:42.851
[gasps]

00:20:43.452 --> 00:20:45.489
And I enjoy being

00:20:45.557 --> 00:20:47.995
a regular student alongside
my sister.

00:20:49.264 --> 00:20:50.867
Me, too, Brother.

00:20:55.376 --> 00:20:57.046
[Tatsuya] So on that note...

00:20:57.948 --> 00:21:01.789
Why don't we go back
to our ordinary lives for today?

00:21:05.764 --> 00:21:08.803
<i>[ELISA singing in Japanese]</i>

00:21:08.870 --> 00:21:15.817
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:21:39.164 --> 00:21:45.442
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:21:45.510 --> 00:21:48.215
<i>♪♪ Shape of my love ♪♪</i>

00:21:48.282 --> 00:21:51.188
<i>[singing in Japanese]</i>

00:21:51.254 --> 00:21:58.101
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:21:58.168 --> 00:22:00.674
<i>♪♪ Eternal song ♪♪</i>

00:22:00.740 --> 00:22:03.847
<i>[singing in Japanese]</i>

00:22:03.913 --> 00:22:10.861
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:22:36.311 --> 00:22:38.516
[buzzing]
[grunts]

00:22:38.583 --> 00:22:41.989
<i>[booming]</i>

00:22:44.528 --> 00:22:45.997
[Masaki exhales]

00:22:50.540 --> 00:22:51.976
[George] Good work in there,
Masaki.

00:22:52.043 --> 00:22:53.345
I'm impressed.

00:22:54.414 --> 00:22:55.984
[grunts]
Thanks, George.

00:22:56.919 --> 00:22:59.424
So, did you hear this news yet?

00:22:59.490 --> 00:23:02.396
<i>[tense music]</i>

00:23:02.463 --> 00:23:04.434
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:23:04.500 --> 00:23:05.971
[Masaki] Imagine that.

00:23:06.037 --> 00:23:08.743
A terrorist invasion over
at First High.

00:23:08.810 --> 00:23:10.547
Although, it looks like
the incident itself

00:23:10.614 --> 00:23:12.584
has already been resolved,
apparently.

00:23:13.185 --> 00:23:15.289
[Masaki] Sounds like there
were casualties.

00:23:15.757 --> 00:23:18.161
Hmm?
You're worried about our rivals?

00:23:18.228 --> 00:23:19.297
[Masaki] No.

00:23:19.364 --> 00:23:20.399
I'm sure that it
was the terrorists

00:23:20.466 --> 00:23:22.103
who sustained the injuries.

00:23:22.236 --> 00:23:23.539
[water shuts off]
This First High,

00:23:23.606 --> 00:23:26.177
home to two direct descendants
of the Ten Master Clans,

00:23:26.244 --> 00:23:27.446
among others.

00:23:27.514 --> 00:23:30.019
I was just wondering if perhaps

00:23:30.085 --> 00:23:33.258
they took it a little overboard
with their defense.

00:23:33.826 --> 00:23:35.830
[laughs]
That's so like you.

00:23:36.699 --> 00:23:38.101
But no matter how powerful

00:23:38.168 --> 00:23:40.807
the First High student body
may be,

00:23:40.874 --> 00:23:44.247
you, Masaki‐‐
the Crimson Prince‐‐

00:23:44.314 --> 00:23:45.917
you have no peer.

00:23:46.384 --> 00:23:47.721
True.

